cs.SE, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with evaluating vulnerability discovery models (VDMs) which are used in software engineering to estimate the total number of vulnerabilities that will be reported after a software is released. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also deals with security-related issues, so it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The methodology proposed in the paper involves empirical evaluation, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper could also be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with vulnerability data of popular web browsers.
